<br>
2) I'd like to see berserk mode revisited as opposed to inventing a new 'gimmick'. It really wasn't implemented very well, and its only purpose on raids is to tell the other clerics that the cleric in your group is sucking.<br>
<br>
Possible ideas would be to raise the hp level in which you berserk at, make it scale with levels... also scale the attack modifier and add a +dmg hit modifier. Right now you berserk at 40% life, you gain a small attack bonus, and all your criticle hits are now crippling blows. I'd like to see the level 60 version make you berserk at maybe 70% life, a much larger +attk bonus, and perhaps make crippling blows do 5 or 6 times stronger hits as opposed to the 4x there is now.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushadowtiger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadowtiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/3/02 9:16:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1984.topic&index=142>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: my 2 thoughts</span><hr size=1> The issues are in the high end game, certainly not the pre-60 game.  At the high end game there are really two situations that warriors have problems with, each with their own set of problems:<br>
<br>
1) In Raid situations: <br>
The line between the warrior and the other tank classes has gotten much fuzzier. <br>
A) SKs and Pallies can taunt a HECK of a lot better than warriors<br>
B) The margin between Warriors and other tanks as far as the ability to tank damage has gotten VERY narrow.  The other classes have narrowed the HP gap considerably, and the AC cap makes that warrior advantage ineffective.<br>
<br>
2) In EXP groups: <br>
<br>
A) Pallies and SKs are doing as much or more damage than warriors, AND they can manage agro better than we can.  <br>
<br>
1) Monks, especially well equipped monks, can tank BETTER than warriors can.  The monk issues are threefold: Monks have better damage avoidance skills, monk HP are approaching Warrior HP at the high end game, and the AC cap makes the Warrior AC advantage a moot point.<br>
<br>
I only see a few alternatives to fix these ballance issues without nerfing any other classes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Better Warrior Damage Mitigation</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Do something to improve the warrior damage mitigation - either fixing the AC cap so that AC would once again MATTER, or giving warriors some sort of special class-based (AAXP?) damage mitigation skill.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Better Warrior Damage Avoidance</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Raise the skill caps for warriors.   Increase Riposte to 250, increase parry to 250, and/or increase the warrior's Dodge cap to 220.  These limits could be raised in the 50-60 caps, or they could be raised through AAXP skills that give bonuses to the various mitigation skills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Better Warrior Damage Output</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Let's put warriors back where they were supposed to be in the 100/120/140 'vision'.  Monks are doing 150%+ damage that Warriors are doing.  Rogues are doing closer to 200% of warrior damage.<br>
<br>
I see three options here:<br>
1) Raise Warrior Dual Wield and Double attack levels to 250/250.  With the advantage that the other classes have with regards to weapon ratios there shouldn't be mush of a problem with raising these caps.<br>
<br>
2) Tweak the offensive discipline timers: 60 minutes is a LONG time to wait for an offensive discipline resuse time.<br>
<br>
3) Put better high-end weapons in the game for warriors - weapons  that have better ratios AND the ability to hold agro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Widening the HP gap - back to where the 'vision' was</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1) Increase the base number of HP that warriors get per point of STA<br>
<br>
2) More warrior-only high HP items.<br>
<br>
3) AAXP skills that build on the ND base - maybe a warrior class skill that adds an EXTRA 10%??<br>
<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts - trying to condense what the issues - or at least the issues as I percieve them.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am not saying we need ALL of these concessions.....just suggestion possible avenues to putting Warriors back to the place where the 'vision' stated they were supposed to be. <p><a target=new href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=331441>Tappy Thistlebloom</a>
