<br>
<br>
IMO this should be taken a step further.  Much like LoH and HT, this should be a *WARRIOR* ability that is on a timer.  Every 2 hours or so the warrior should be able to use this ability once.  100 percent chance of success, come back with 50 percent HP and Buffs (Somewhat like Divine Intervention).<br>
<br>
This is a actual *fix* to warriors being more desirable in a group (for some reason your hp goes below 0, your group isnt screwed (Think CT etc.) or if you are duoing etc.  This will put warriors themselves back in demand for the best choice for an actual tank in a group in my opinion.  It would also be pretty damn cool.  *soandso's ironwill overcomes the force of death itself*.<br>
<br>
For raiding situations, this should stack with DI, (DI should be used first before this) which would allow warriors to once again have some advantage while being the MT while at the same time, not unbalancing the game by giving the warrior more HP.  (More hp cant be given for simple reasons, those being that certain enounters will become too trivial if the warrior has too many hp)  This in itself gives the warrior *more hp* without actually giving the warrior more hp for the CH rotation to heal. Also, 125 HP is the max HP that can be placed on ANY item with VI's current coding system (this will NOT be changed in PoP).<br>
<br>
This would affect warriors of all level, 1 - 60 and all levels of equipment (podank 3000 unbuffed tanks to 6000 unbuffed tanks).  This would NOT unbalance the current CH rotation issue that VI has.  (They arent going to be giving much more HP for warriors to have in a CH rotation FACE IT)<br>
<br>
In addition to this Offensive and Defensive timers should be on a seperate timer, fellstrike and mightystrike should be reduced to 10 and 20 minutes respectively, aggressive from 30 to 15.<br>
<br>
Probably leaving alot of stuff out, its hella late.<br>
<br>
Paladins have their abilities, SK's, monks, rogues, rangers have theirs, I think its about time they gave warriors something that is actually useful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugalarianizuber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galarian iz uber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/02 3:27:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1984.topic&index=147>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   kikou</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Paladins have their abilities, SK's, monks, rogues, rangers have theirs, I think its about time they gave warriors something that is actually useful. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
